gomodel:SYNGO_1607  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 3 shows that alpha-internexin concentrates in the PSD fraction upon cell fractionation of rat forebrain. This is verified by immuno-EM (DAB method) in Figure 6 where staining is only observed at the post-synaptic side, the presynaptic side remaining relatively clean. No quantification is offered. The authors comment \"Immunoreactivity [of alpha-internexin) was clearly localized in the dendrites, spines and in most but not all PSDs (Fig. 6). Presynaptic structures were not stained. The specificity of the staining was confirmed by the lack of stainings with non-immune rabbit immunoglobulins (not shown).\" p78\nThis seems also to hold in mouse brain, see additional reference.. Experimental description: Figure legend: \"Subcellular distribution of a-internexin in the rat forebrain...\" and M&M: \"Male Wistar rats (4 weeks old) were examined immunohistochemically at both the light and electron microscopic levels. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1607" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

